For advanced configuration, PM2 uses an ecosystem file:

```javascript
module.exports = {
  apps : [{
    name: 'my-app',
    script: 'app.js',
    instances: 'max',
    exec_mode: 'cluster',
    env: {
      NODE_ENV: 'production',
      PORT: 3000
    },
    log_file: 'logs/app.log',
    error_file: 'logs/err.log',
    out_file: 'logs/out.log'
  }]
};
```

Run with: `pm2 start ecosystem.config.js`.
